## 2. EmulatorBridge — exact Obj-C++ API (each method → the vAmiga call it wraps)

Design rule: **the `.h` is pure Obj-C** (no `vamiga::` types, no C++). All C++ lives in the `.mm` behind a `VAmiga *_emu;` ivar and an internal `vamiga::Emulator*` cached as `_inner = _emu->amiga.emu;`. Enums crossing to Swift are plain `NSInteger`/`typedef NS_ENUM`. The bridge runs a private serial queue (`_emuQueue`, a real pthread for tight pacing) that owns both control ops and the frame tick.

### Lifecycle

| Bridge method | Wraps |
|---|---|
| `+ (instancetype)shared` | singleton holding `_emu = new VAmiga()` |
| `- (void)bootWithConfig:` | `_emu->launch(self, &bridgeListener)` (`VAmiga.h:1887`; `Callback = void(const void*, Message)` `MsgQueueTypes.h:289`), then set defaults + `ConfigScheme`/`Opt`s (see init seq below), then `_inner->update()` |
| `- (void)start` | spawns the emu pthread → run-loop §3; first sets `_emu->run()` (`VAmiga.h:1759`) once ROM ready |
| `- (void)pause` | `_emu->pause()` (`VAmiga.h:1767`) + `_inner->update()` |
| `- (void)resume` | `_emu->run()` (`VAmiga.h:1759`) + `audioPort.port->unmute(10000)` (`main.cpp:2671`) |
| `- (void)hardReset` / `softReset` | `_emu->hardReset()` / `softReset()` (`VAmiga.h:1774/1780`) |
| `- (void)shutdown` | stop pthread → `_emu->halt(); delete _emu;` (`VAmiga.h:1788`) |
| `- (BOOL)isReady` | `try { _emu->isReady(); return YES; } catch(AppError&) { return NO; }` (`VAmiga.h:1729`; throws `Fault::ROM_MISSING`/`CHIP_RAM_MISSING`) |
| state props `isPoweredOn/isRunning/isPaused/isWarping` | `_emu->isPoweredOn()` etc. (`VAmiga.h:1694-1722`) |

Init sequence (mirror `main.cpp:778-801`, run on `_emuQueue` before first ROM load):
```objc
_emu->launch(self, &bridgeListener);
_emu->set(ConfigScheme::A500_OCS_1MB);            // VAmiga.h:1921 (AmigaTypes.h:154)
_emu->set(Opt::AUD_VOLL, 100); _emu->set(Opt::AUD_VOLR, 100);
_emu->set(Opt::MEM_CHIP_RAM, 512); _emu->set(Opt::MEM_SLOW_RAM, 512);
_emu->set(Opt::AGNUS_REVISION, (i64)AgnusRevision::OCS);
_emu->set(Opt::DRIVE_CONNECT, true, 1);           // connect df1
_emu->set(Opt::HOST_SAMPLE_RATE,
          (i64)AVAudioSession.sharedInstance.sampleRate);  // main.cpp:2211
_inner->update();
```

### Framebuffer accessor (called from the renderer / CADisplayLink thread)

```objc
// dims are compile-time constants exposed to Swift:
//   kAmigaWidth = 912 (HPIXELS)  kAmigaHeight = 313 (VPIXELS)
//   kAmigaBytesPerRow = 3648     pixelFormat = MTLPixelFormatRGBA8Unorm
- (const uint32_t *)lockFrameNr:(int64_t *)nr lof:(BOOL *)lof prevLof:(BOOL *)prevLof;
    // _emu->videoPort.lockTexture();
    // const u32* p = _emu->videoPort.getTexture(&n,&l,&pl);  (VAmiga.h:1131)
    // *nr=n; *lof=l; *prevLof=pl; return p;
- (void)unlockFrame;   // _emu->videoPort.unlockTexture();
```

**Format (verified):** `Texel == u32` (`FrameBufferTypes.h:31`, TPP=1). Built via `HI_HI_LO_LO(0xFF,b,g,r)` → memory byte order **R,G,B,A** little-endian → Metal `MTLPixelFormatRGBA8Unorm` with NO swizzle (web uploads as GL_RGBA/UNSIGNED_BYTE verbatim). Buffer is **always 912×313**, stride **3648 B**, total **1,141,824 B**, regardless of mode. Active picture is a crop: start fixed (`xOff=12,yOff=12`, w≈876) then optionally call `videoPort.findInnerArea(x1,x2,y1,y2)` (`VAmiga.h:1135`) once stabilized. Per MEMORY.md, mirror apple2ts framing/aspect — render full texture into a Metal source tex, crop with tex coords, present at 4:3 with height line-doubled.

**Locking is mandatory here** (unlike the web single-thread build): the renderer reads on the display thread while the pthread runs `computeFrame()` → `swapBuffers()` (`PixelEngine.cpp:231-248`) under the same `textureLock`. Skip re-upload when `nr` is unchanged.

### Keyboard

```objc
- (void)keyDown:(uint8_t)amigaCode;  // _emu->put(Cmd::KEY_PRESS,   KeyCmd{amigaCode,0,0});
- (void)keyUp:(uint8_t)amigaCode;    // _emu->put(Cmd::KEY_RELEASE, KeyCmd{amigaCode,0});
- (void)keyReleaseAll;               // _emu->put(Cmd::KEY_RELEASE_ALL);
```
`KeyCode = u8` (`Aliases.h:35`) is the **raw Amiga hardware keycode, NOT ASCII**. Use the **command-queue path** (`put`, thread-safe, `Amiga.cpp:941-947`) — not the direct `keyboard.press` the web build uses (that's only race-free in single-threaded WASM). Host must translate. Provide `AmigaKeymap` mapping `UIKeyboardHIDUsage` → Amiga code from the canonical table in `js/vAmiga_keyboard.js:168-283` (itself a copy of vAmiga's `GUI/Peripherals/AmigaKey.swift`). Anchors: A–Z = 0x10–0x28 spread, digits 0x01–0x0A, Return 0x44, Space 0x40, Backspace 0x41, Esc 0x45, F1–F10 0x50–0x59, arrows 0x4C–0x4F, ShiftL/R 0x60/0x61, CtrlL 0x63, AltL/R 0x64/0x65, **leftAmiga 0x66 / rightAmiga 0x67** (no HID equivalent → on-screen buttons), keypad brackets 0x5A/0x5B (on-screen).

