```objc
- (void)mouseMovePort:(int)p dx:(double)dx dy:(double)dy;
    // _emu->put(Cmd::MOUSE_MOVE_REL, CoordCmd{p, dx, dy});
- (void)mouseButtonPort:(int)p button:(int)b pressed:(BOOL)d;
    // _emu->put(Cmd::MOUSE_BUTTON, GamePadCmd{p, d?PRESS_LEFT:RELEASE_LEFT});  (MIDDLE/RIGHT for b=2/3)
```
Relative deltas from finger drags. Device auto-selects MOUSE on any mouse event (`Mouse.cpp:220`), so no port pre-config. Convention: mouse on port 1, joystick on port 2; expose a UI toggle.

### Joystick (port 0/1)

```objc
- (void)joyPort:(int)p action:(NSInteger)gamePadAction;
    // _emu->put(Cmd::JOY_EVENT, GamePadCmd{p, (GamePadAction)gamePadAction});
```
`GamePadAction` (`JoystickTypes.h:31-52`, declaration-order values 0..18): `PULL_UP=0,PULL_DOWN,PULL_LEFT,PULL_RIGHT,PRESS_FIRE,...,RELEASE_X,RELEASE_Y,RELEASE_XY,RELEASE_FIRE,...`. Mirror these as a Swift-visible `NS_ENUM` so the UI sends ints. D-pad model is per-axis: down→`PULL_*`, up→`RELEASE_X`/`RELEASE_Y` (or `RELEASE_XY` on full release); fire→`PRESS_FIRE`/`RELEASE_FIRE`. Autofire via `set(Opt::JOY_AUTOFIRE,true,portId)`.

### Disk insert / eject

```objc
- (BOOL)insertDiskData:(NSData *)d intoDrive:(int)n writeProtected:(BOOL)wp error:(NSError**)e;
    // build typed file from bytes, then df[n]->insertMedia(file, wp):
    //   const u8* buf=d.bytes; isize len=d.length;
    //   if (ADFFile::isCompatible(buf,len))  { ADFFile  f{buf,len}; _emu->df[n].insertMedia(f, wp); }
    //   else if (ADZFile::isCompatible(...)) { ADZFile  f{...}; ... }   // also DMS/EADF/EXE/ST/IMG
    //   wrap try/catch(AppError&) → NSError{ domain, code=(NSInteger)e.fault(), FaultEnum::key(...) }
- (void)ejectDrive:(int)n;     // if (_emu->df[n].getInfo().hasDisk) _emu->df[n].ejectDisk();
- (BOOL)hasDiskInDrive:(int)n; // _emu->df[n].getInfo().hasDisk
```
Use the **public `FloppyDriveAPI`** (`VAmiga.h:688/699`), not `drive->swapDisk` (web-only). df0 accepts **DD only**; for HD set `Opt::DRIVE_TYPE = HD_35` on df1-3 first. Detection table: `ADFFile/ADZFile/DMSFile/EADFFile/EXEFile/STFile/IMGFile` each expose `static isCompatible(buf,len)` (see `main.cpp:1480-1528`). ADF DD size = 901120. Messages `Msg::DISK_INSERT/EJECT/PROTECTED`, `DRIVE_LED/MOTOR/STEP` fire on the listener.

