ROM must be flashed **while powered off** (`main.cpp:1766-1813`). `ALLOW_ALL_ROMS=1` so any 512K blob is accepted. There is **no core "ROM_MISSING" message** — derive readiness from `isReady()` throwing and publish your own state.

### Pause/resume + snapshot save/load

```objc
- (NSData *)takeSnapshot;
    // MediaFile* s = _emu->amiga.takeSnapshot();             (VAmiga.h:75 — caller OWNS)
    // u8* p = (u8*)((Snapshot*)s)->getHeader(); isize n = s->getSize();
    // NSData* out = [NSData dataWithBytes:p length:n]; delete s; return out;
- (BOOL)loadSnapshotData:(NSData *)d error:(NSError**)e;
