Messages `Msg::SNAPSHOT_TAKEN/RESTORED` confirm. Snapshot version is 4.3.1; mismatch throws `SNAP_*` faults.

### Audio (set up inside the bridge, pulled on the RT audio thread — no Swift surface)

`AVAudioEngine` source node (or `AURenderCallback`), interleaved float32 stereo at the session rate:
```objc
isize got = _emu->audioPort.copyInterleaved(outBuffer, frameCount);   // VAmiga.h:1025
// zero-fill (frameCount-got) on underrun
```
Set `Opt::HOST_SAMPLE_RATE` to `AVAudioSession.sampleRate` (≈48000) at boot and on route change, then `update()`. Keep Adaptive Sample Rate on (`Opt::AUD_ASR` default) so the ring buffer (4096 `SamplePair`s, `AudioPort.h:130`) tracks the 50/60 fps producer without under/overflow.

### Listener (C callback → marshal to main)

```objc
static void bridgeListener(const void *ctx, vamiga::Message msg) {
    EmulatorBridge *self = (__bridge EmulatorBridge *)ctx;
    // decode msg.type + the right union member (MsgQueueTypes.h:266-282)
    dispatch_async(dispatch_get_main_queue(), ^{ /* update AppModel @Published */ });
}
```
Acts on: `Msg::VIDEO_FORMAT` → set `target_fps` 50/60 + republish; `VIEWPORT` → crop rect (`msg.viewport.hstrt/vstrt/hstop/vstop`); `DRIVE_LED/MOTOR/STEP` (`msg.drive.nr/value`); `DISK_INSERT/EJECT/PROTECTED`; `POWER/RUN/PAUSE`. Fires on the emu thread — always `dispatch_async` to main before touching UI.

