## 4. project.yml — sources, excludes, build settings

Compile **everything** in `vAmiga/Core` except the 4 files below. You cannot drop `RemoteServers/` or `Recorder/` — `Amiga` owns `RemoteManager remoteManager` as a member (`Amiga.h:145`, `CLONE` at `:253`) and Agnus/Denise reference the recorder; dropping them = link errors. They are inert at runtime (never start a server; `FFmpeg.cpp` just probes nonexistent paths). `httplib.h`/`Socket.h` take the POSIX branch on iOS and compile clean. **No `ios_stubs.cpp` needed** — the core is already host-driven and platform-clean (zero SDL/GL/X11/emscripten.h in Core).

**Excludes (exactly 4, all have their own `main()` or are dead):**
`Headless.cpp`, `Headless.h`, `ThirdParty/xdms/xdms.c`, `ThirdParty/xdms/_old_pfile.c`.

**Required ThirdParty (keep compiling):** `lz4.c` (snapshot compression — save-states need it), `xdms/*.c` minus the two above (`.dms` decode). **zlib:** define `USE_ZLIB=1` + link `libz.tbd` for gzip in `Compression.cpp` (recommended), or omit both and lose gzip (lz4 still works).

