## 5. Phased milestones

- **M1 — Builds + boots to insert-disk screen.** xcodegen project, all 167 core sources compile + link arm64, ROM bundled and loaded via `loadKickstartData`, emu pthread runs `update()`/`computeFrame()` at 50 Hz, MetalRenderer uploads the 912×313 RGBA8 texture, you see the Kickstart hand/insert-disk animation. Exit: framebuffer renders and animates; `isReady()==YES`.
- **M2 — Disk + input.** `.fileImporter` → `insertDiskData` into df0; boot a real DD `.adf`; keyboard (HID→Amiga keymap via `Cmd::KEY_PRESS/RELEASE`), mouse (`MOUSE_MOVE_REL`/`MOUSE_BUTTON`), joystick (`JOY_EVENT`). Listener drives drive-LED + disk-state UI. Exit: a game boots and is controllable.
- **M3 — Audio.** `AVAudioEngine` source node pulling `copyInterleaved`; `HOST_SAMPLE_RATE` set to session rate; ASR on; unmute on resume. Exit: in-game audio, no underruns at 48 kHz.
- **M4 — Save states.** `takeSnapshot`→`NSData`→disk; `loadSnapshotData` with `Snapshot::isCompatible` gate and corrupt-snapshot recovery (it hard-resets + rethrows). Exit: round-trip save/restore mid-game.
- **M5 — Full input-mode UI.** Port the sibling apps' InputArea modes: keyboard / joystick / d-pad / touch / **side-panel** (`.panelKeys`) with per-orientation d-pad button positions (per MEMORY.md `project-landscape-input.md`: side-panel is a new mode, added not substituted). Plus port toggle (mouse↔joystick), leftAmiga/rightAmiga/keypad-bracket on-screen buttons, warp toggle.

